en.quote1: "Don't cry because it's over, smile because it happened."\n- Dr. Cat Seuss -
en.quote2: "You only live once, but if you do it right, once is enough."\n- Mae Cat West -
en.quote3: "In three words I can sum up everything I've learned about life: it goes on."\n- Robert Cat Frost -
en.quote4: "To live is the rarest thing in the world. Most people exist, that is all."\n- Oscar Cat Wilde -
en.quote5: "It is better to be hated for what you are than to be loved for what you are not."\n- André Cat Gide -
en.quote6: "Life is what happens to you while you're busy making other plans."\n- Allen Cat Saunders -
en.quote7: "Sometimes the questions are complicated and the answers are simple."\n- Dr. Cat Seuss -
en.quote8: "I'm not afraid of death; I just don't want to be there when it happens."\n- Woody Cat Allen -
en.quote9: "Everything you can imagine is real."\n- Pablo Cat Picasso -
en.quote10: "Life is like riding a bicycle. To keep your balance, you must keep moving."\n- Albert Cat Einstein -
en.quote11: "Life isn't about finding yourself. Life is about creating yourself."\n- George Bernard Cat Shaw -
en.quote12: "I'm the one that's got to die when it's time for me to die, so let me live my life the way I want to."\n- Jimi Cat Hendrix -
en.quote13: ""You are already naked. There is no reason not to follow your heart."\n- Steve Cat Jobs -
en.quote14: "Things change. And friends leave. Life doesn't stop for anybody."\n- Stephen Cat Chbosky -
en.quote15: "The fear of death follows from the fear of life. A man who lives fully is prepared to die at any time."\n- Mark Cat Twain -
en.quote16: "The one you love and the one who loves you are never, ever the same person."\n- Chuck Cat Palahniuk -
en.quote17: "If you don't know where you're going, any road'll take you there"\n- George Cat Harrison -
en.quote18: "We are what we pretend to be, so we must be careful about what we pretend to be."\n- Kurt Cat Vonnegut -
en.quote19: "Some infinities are bigger than other infinities."\n- John Cat Green -
en.quote20: "Life's hard. It's even harder when you're stupid."\n- John Cat Wayne -
en.quote21: "Death ends a life, not a relationship."\n- Mitch Cat Albom -
en.quote22: "Fear is a part of life, if you live, you fear."\n- Cat Diablo 3 -
en.quote23: "Where there is love there is life."\n- Mahatma Cat Gandhi -
en.quote24: "You cannot find peace by avoiding life."\n- Virginia Cat Woolf -
en.quote25: "We have to dare to be ourselves, however frightening or strange that self may prove to be."\n- May Cat Sarton -
en.quote26: "Anyone who lives within their means suffers from a lack of imagination."\n- Oscar Cat Wilde -
en.quote27: "Get busy living or get busy dying."\n- Stephen Cat King -
en.quote28: "May you live every day of your life."\n- Jonathan Cat Swift -
en.quote29: "Life can only be understood backwards; but it must be lived forwards."\n- Søren Cat Kierkegaard -
en.quote30: "Do not go where the path may lead, go instead where there is no path and leave a trail."\n- Ralph Waldo Cat Emerson -
en.quote31: "If my life is going to mean anything, I have to live it myself."\n- Rick Cat Riordan -
en.quote32: "It is said that your life flashes before your eyes just before you die. That is true, it's called Life."\n- Terry Cat Pratchett -
en.quote33: "Life is to be enjoyed, not endured"\n- Gordon B. Cat Hinckley -
en.quote34: "Tell the truth, or someone will tell it for you."\n- Stephanie Cat Klein -
en.quote35: "Monsters are real, and ghosts are real too. They live inside us, and sometimes, they win."\n- Stephen Cat King -
en.quote36: "The more I see, the less I know for sure."\n- John Cat Lennon -
en.quote37: "If I can stop one heart from breaking, I shall not live in vain."\n- Emily Cat Dickinson -
en.quote38: "The most wasted of all days is one without laughter."\n- E.E. Cat Cummings -
en.quote39: "Unbeing dead isn't being alive."\n- E.E. Cat Cummings -
en.quote40: "Some people have lives; some people have music."\n- John Cat Green -
en.quote41: "This is your life and its ending one moment at a time."\n- Chuck Cat Palahniuk -
en.quote42: "I've got nothing to do today but smile."\n- Paul Cat-Simon -
en.quote43: "That it will never come again is what makes life so sweet."\n- Emily Cat Dickinson -
en.quote44: "Do I not destroy my enemies when I make them my friends?"\n- Abraham Cat Lincoln -
en.quote45: "No persons are more frequently wrong, than those who will not admit they are wrong."\n- François de La Cat Rochefoucauld -
en.quote46: "Life is a book and there are a thousand pages I have not yet read."\n- Cassandra Cat Clare -
en.quote47: "I don't like people who have never fallen or stumbled"\n- Boris Cat Pasternak -
en.quote48: "The past has no power over the present moment."\n- Eckhart Cat-Tolle -
en.quote49: "The trouble is if you don’t spend your life yourself, other people spend it for you."\n- Peter Cat Shaffer -
en.quote50: "There's nowhere you can be that isn't where you're meant to be..."\n- John Cat Lennon -
en.quote51: "You can have it all. Just not all at once."\n- Oprah Cat-Winfrey -
en.quote52: "I'll try anything once, twice if I like it, three times to make sure."\n- Mae Cat West -
en.quote53: "This is your life. Do what you want and do it often."\n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote54: "If you don't like something, change it."\n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote55: "If you don't like your job, quit."n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote56: "Stop over-analysing, life is simple."\n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote57: "All emotions are beautiful."\n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote58: "When you eat, appreciate every last bite."\n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote60: "Open your heart, mind and arms to new things and people, we are united in our differences."\n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote61: "Ask the next person you see what their passion is and share your inspiring dream with them."\n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote62: "Travel often; getting lost will help you find yourself."\n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote63: "Some opportunities only come once, seize them."\n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote64: "Life is about the people you meet and the things you create with them, so go out and start creating."\n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote65: "Life is short, live your dream and wear your passion.”\n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote66: "Things don’t have to change the world to be important."\n- Steve Cat Jobs -
en.quote67: "Weather forecast for tonight: dark."\n- George CatCarlin -
en.quote68: "And yet death is the destination we all share."\n- Steve Cat Jobs -
en.quote69: "Sometimes life is going to hit you in the head with a brick. Don’t lose faith."\n- Steve Cat Jobs -
en.quote70: "Your time is limited, so don’t waste it living someone else’s life."\n- Steve Cat Jobs -
en.quote71: "Let’s go invent tomorrow instead of worrying about what happened yesterday."\n- Steve Cat Jobs -
en.quote72: "Stay hungry. Stay foolish."\n- Steve Cat Jobs -
en.quote73: "The best way to pay for a lovely moment is to enjoy it."\n- Richard Cat Bach -
en.quote74: "We become what we think about."\n– Earl Cat Nightingale -
en.quote75: "Everything has beauty, but not everyone can see."\n– Cat Confucius -
en.quote76: "When I let go of what I am, I become what I might be."\n– Lao Cat Tzu -
en.quote77: "Fall seven times and stand up eight."\n– Japanese Cat Proverb -
en.quote78: "The best revenge is massive success."\n– Frank Cat Sinatra -
en.quote79: "Either you run the day, or the day runs you."\n– Jim Cat Rohn -
en.quote80: "Too many of us are not living our dreams because we are living our fears."\n– Les Cat Brown -
en.quote81: "If you want to lift yourself up, lift up someone else."\n- Booker T. Cat Washington -
en.quote82: "There are no traffic jams along the extra mile."\n- Roger Cat Staubach -
en.quote83: "It is never too late to be what you might have been."\n- George Cat Eliot -
en.quote84: "I would rather die of passion than of boredom."\n- Vincent van Cat Gogh -
en.quote85: "Do what you can, where you are, with what you have."\n- Teddy Cat Roosevelt -
en.quote86: "The question isn’t who is going to let me; it’s who is going to stop me."\n- Ayn Cat Rand -
en.quote87: "Life is what we make it, always has been, always will be."\n- Grandma Cat Moses -
en.quote88: "If you can dream it, you can achieve it."\n- Zig Cat Ziglar -
en.quote89: "Life is 10% what happens to me and 90% of how I react to it."\n- Charles Cat Swindoll -
en.quote90: "The past is a ghost, the future a dream. All we ever have is now."\n- Bill Cat Cosby -
en.quote91: "You miss 100% of the shots you don’t take."\n- Wayne Cat Gretzky -
en.quote92: "Whether you think you can or you think you can’t, you’re right."\n- Henry Cat Ford -
en.quote93: "The only way to do great work is to love what you do."\n- Steve Cat Jobs -
en.quote94: "Build your own dreams, or someone else will hire you to build theirs."\n- Farrah Cat Gray -
en.quote95: "Whatever the mind of man can conceive and believe, it can achieve."\n- Napoleon Cat Hill -
en.quote96: "Believe you can and you’re halfway there."\n- Theodore Cat Roosevelt -
en.quote97: "Everything you’ve ever wanted is on the other side of fear."\n- George Cat Addair -
en.quote98: "The only person you are destined to become is the person you decide to be."\n- Ralph Waldo Cat Emerson -
en.quote99: "Knowing others is wisdom, knowing yourself is Enlightenment."\n- Lao Cat Tzu -
en.quote100: "The journey of a thousand miles begins with one step."\n- Lao Cat Tzu -
en.quote101: "From caring comes courage."\n- Lao Cat Tzu -
en.quote102: "He who obtains has little. He who scatters has much."\n- Lao Cat Tzu -
en.quote103: "Nothing is softer or more flexible than water, yet nothing can resist it."\n- Lao Cat Tzu -
en.quote104: "“Count your age by friends, not years. Count your life by smiles, not tears."\n- John Cat Lennon -
en.quote105: “Happiness only real when shared.”\n- Christopher Cat McCandless -
